{
  "texts": [
    "Since ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is complete, X exists in ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩, and since X ⊆ S, ⊥ ̸ ∈ X, so X exists in ⟨S, ⊑⟩.",
    "Now we claim that X = ↓ X, so X is a principal downset.",
    "Since X ⊆ ↓ X is immediate, we need only show that ↓ X ⊆ X.",
    "By persistence, it suffices to show that X ∈ X.",
    "If X ̸ ∈ X, then refinability in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ implies that there is an x ∈ S such that x ⊑ X and for all x ′ ⊑ x, x ′ ̸ ∈ X."
  ]
}